                    <td width="2%"  valign="top" >&nbsp;</td>
                    <td width="98%"><p>The <a href="nebosh.php">NEBOSH</a> International Certificate in Fire Safety and Risk Management is a new qualification for the professionals responsible for fire safety in their workplace. NEBOSH International Fire Safety and Risk Management certificate course established globally as a popular qualification and the candidates accomplished this <a href="Credentials.php">qualification</a> will evolve fire safety to minimize injuries, fatalities and property damage in their workplace.</p>
					<p>It is suitable for Fire marshals, <a href="http://www.nist.co.in/Fire-Services.php" target="_blank">Fire safety Advisors</a>, Managers, Supervisors and Safety representatives who need to ensure that their organization meets its standard under fire safety regulations. Crucially, the practical element of the course also ensures that participants can carry out unaided fire risk assessment and prepare a recommendations report for management.</p>
     					
 </td>
                      
                  </tr>	
					<tr>
                    <td width="3%"  valign="top" >&nbsp;</td>
                    <td width="70%"><p>Is this Qualification Recognized?</p>
                      <p>The NEBOSH qualification meets the academic requirements to apply for Technician <a href="Membership.php">membership</a> (Tech IOSH) of the <a href="training_IOSH.php">Institution of Occupational Safety and Health </a>(IOSH), and Associate membership (AIIRSM) of the<a href="http://www.iirsm.org/"> International Institute of Risk and Safety Management </a>(IIRSM)makes this qualification highly recognized worldwide.
					  </p></td>
                    <td width="4%"  valign="top" >&nbsp;</td>
                  </tr>				  
				  
				  <tr>
                    <td width="3%"  valign="top" >&nbsp;</td>
                    <td width="70%"><p>Benefits: <p>
                      <p>Professionals who have fire safety responsibilities at work, particularly whose task to carry out fire risk assessments and preventing loss of life and property damage should take the <a href="http://www.nebosh.org.uk/Qualifications/Certificate/default.asp?cref=984&ct=2" target="_blank">Fire safety and Risk Management.</a></p>
<p>The damage caused by fire all over the world is $630 billion per annum. To lessen the loss caused by fire devastation NEBOSH as developed this specialized qualification.<p>
 </td>
                    <td width="4%"  valign="top" >&nbsp;</td>
                  </tr>				  
